    "rating": 4.6,
    "reviews": [
      {
        "author_name": "Anura Hotel",
        "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105276182439302810796/reviews",
        "language": "en",
        "original_language": "en",
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrNpsEqssqDq03zKb4V_Nvg87mcQPGmUztdzq6zxByjEo4Qg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo",
        "rating": 5,
        "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
        "text": "The New French Kiss sets a high bar—and clears it comfortably.\n\nTony is an exceptional host. No theatrics, just sharp awareness, good timing, and genuine care. You feel looked after without it ever becoming intrusive. That’s professional hospitality.\n\nThe food is superb. Well-balanced, properly executed, and clearly built on quality ingredients rather than gimmicks. Each plate lands exactly where it should—confident and clean.\n\nThe setting does a lot of heavy lifting too. The view is outstanding, and it elevates the whole experience from “good meal” to something more memorable. At one point I was even fishing directly from the restaurant—caught a squid, returned it (we’d already eaten and were heading out), but it says everything about the place. It’s not just dinner, it’s an experience.\n\nBottom line: The New French Kiss isn’t trying too hard—it just gets it right.",
        "time": 1777625311,
        "translated": false
      },
      {
        "author_name": "D B",
        "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102591089604829815196/reviews",
        "language": "en",
        "original_language": "en",
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0XciLJlabHZjoIqPE_OxcixDmHUFrJX_F_0j9TJ4OTC2J9g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
        "rating": 4,
        "relative_time_description": "a year ago",
        "text": "Ate here one night after completing all of the restaurants at the Conrad.\n\nThe food was fresh, had nice flavours and came very quick.\n\nIf you want a nice location looking out to the ocean , good local food (with European options available) it’s worth popping down.\n\nWe had squid and spring rolls to start\nChicken penang curry\nChicken and cashew nut\nNoddles with shrimp\nWhich came with 2 large portions of rice\nProfiterolls and the frozen macron\n\nAnd a couple of drinks which came to B2100 which was quite pricy for local food but a lot cheaper than the Conrad",
        "time": 1749005224,
        "translated": false
      },
      {
        "author_name": "ainhoa Dorca",
        "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100343974876201273897/reviews",
        "language": "en",
        "original_language": "en",
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUvZvRrPcay4_zSmxeNenPq76CdtwPEZOlut96TPz8sMs_-vEJ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
        "rating": 5,
        "relative_time_description": "4 months ago",
        "text": "This restaurant is amazing, the food is so so good. We tried a Pad Thai and French fries and were the best of all our trip. The place is so magic and authentic, you can have the bests sunsets there. Also, the staff is so nice and they have some little doggy’s super cute. I recommend a lot this restaurant, we will repeat for sure!",
        "time": 1770937913,
        "translated": false
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Lee Soon Guan",
        "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113004264015161039683/reviews",
        "language": "en",
        "original_language": "en",
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDijVH9tRu4cBtjZSDaSir__GMiLXQbzh7odmE4et-oYIDkoM5sw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7",
        "rating": 5,
        "relative_time_description": "a year ago",
        "text": "Incredibly charming restaurant set close to the beach. Unadulterated view of the calm sea. Drink a glass of wine and enjoy the scenery. When hungry, order from the menu with a variety of local and international fare at very reasonable price. You won't regret it. Go fishing or snorkeling? That can be arranged. Friendly service but abrupt sometimes especially from one particular staff. Good food, relaxing...Antoine is the main man from Belgium!",
        "time": 1750686823,
        "translated": false
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Sabai Glamping",
        "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102130940928665428032/reviews",
        "language": "en",
        "original_language": "en",
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeiiEmfN83Dtrqvd--KFfc8Rq-fQn6pps4cgz3M8HcyYdkV4gQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
        "rating": 5,
        "relative_time_description": "9 months ago",
        "text": "Great fresh fish in a beautiful unique spot ! Belgian fries were so yummy too. Definitely a place to discover !",
        "time": 1758774653,
        "translated": false
      }
